  "texts": [
    "This difference in what constitutes \"clarity\" could explain the misalignment observed in the Clarity aspect questions, as the SMEs preferred concise and easily digestible information over exhaustive detail.",
    "Particularly in the mental health domain, the LLMs missed that an overflow of information, even if inaccurate, may overwhelm or confuse clients and could harm their understanding.",
    "Theme 3:Referring to Professional Guidance and Tone.",
    "SMEs in both domains favored responses that referred to professional guidance and emphasized the importance of consulting with trained professionals.",
    "In the dietitian domain, responses that encouraged people to seek personalized long-term meal plans or advice from registered dietitians or healthcare providers were favored, as these professionals can tailor recommendations to the individual's unique health needs."
